The "id" field is more likely to be a serially or randomly generated value that is assigned to the data object as it is created in a system.

identifier.description: A 'business' identifier or accession number for the entity, typically as provided by an external system or authority, that are globally unique and persist across implementing systems. Also, since these identifiers are created outside the information system through a specific business process, the Identifier type has additional attributes to capture this additional metadata so the actual identifier values are qualified by the context that created those values. This additional context allows "identifier" instances to be transmitted as business data across systems while still being able to trace them back to the system of origin.

treatment_dose.description: The amount of the treatment given.

treatment_effect.description: The effect of a treatment on the diagnosis or tumor.

treatment_frequency.description: The frequency of using the substance described by this instance.

treatment_intent.description: The medical intent of the treatment.

treatment_outcome.description: The final outcome of the treatment.

treatment_type.description: The type of treatment administered, which may include medication/therapeutics or other procedures.
